The ANC has faced serious criticism within its own ranks that it has regressed and become more tribalistic and even racist in its outlook. ANC deputy secretary-general Jessie Duarte discusses this topic. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - ANC Deputy Secretary-General Jessie Duarte' has warned her party about racist and tribal tendencies. Duarte has recently critiqued the ANC for marginalising people who weren't black Africans. She says the ANC itself is a non-racial party but must guard against side-lining minority race groups. Duarte was speaking to Karima Brown's show The Fix. Watch the full interview above